<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-56716598-C571-4F19-B3B1-E4574A3E542C" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-56716598-C571-4F19-B3B1-E4574A3E542C" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">19 Load a take-up roll core onto the roll winder</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-2F91BA49-2FCE-4F45-840D-45844DC0D9F9"><p class="- topic/p ">When you want to wind media, you must load a take-up roll core onto the roll winder first. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="SECTION_AD5E7C9422384504B87529A62483DF57" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><note type="important" id="GUID-02D8F8CE-6CDE-4A61-9AE9-AED227B7C877" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you use the core of an empty media roll with the same width or wider as the media you are printing on. 
</p></note></section><steps id="GUID-3A47507F-0BAF-44DC-A85E-2352026E926E" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="STEP_F56F97E6C7814348A8CC29ACFEB5BD69" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Locate the winder on the media output side. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_68A247FE1EC34D15A935B6D9C7EAB9A8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EAF70192-0A17-4604-BE9C-C3ED00B89C20-low.png" id="IMAGE_646CF61C148A42C1AE3B708D6DE345B7" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EAF70192-0A17-4604-BE9C-C3ED00B89C20-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_D57B537E149E4426AE225C40E523637A" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Push the green levers on both sides of the take-up media shaft. Remove the take-up media shaft from the winder. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_385FA874200C4DE38656AE5E9507ACF9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FF23CBC6-53BC-4B56-A5F5-2F3CB753E1E9-low.png" id="IMAGE_10F462FC56394BFDA3860E9E5C7511A9" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FF23CBC6-53BC-4B56-A5F5-2F3CB753E1E9-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_DBE0477A2F274B6EAC253316197922DE" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Pull the handle of the locking mechanism inside the core towards you. Take the empty media roll core and slide it on the media shaft. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_4CA2444A74E243B792CBE4CBD1730F13" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BB608C8B-6038-4625-9525-2C6B7F139370-low.png" id="IMAGE_27701AC1CA334A098AED8C30ACB7CCF0" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BB608C8B-6038-4625-9525-2C6B7F139370-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_BE8B06961FD246E79EA783661A051955" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Center the core on the media shaft. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_3CB8437FE6694AD39EC742B18A36CCAA" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-65FD5D48-A424-46E5-9746-8717EF97A269-low.png" id="IMAGE_74C73C83B925450B9B1F745DE5C26AA8" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-65FD5D48-A424-46E5-9746-8717EF97A269-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_9FD039BFA72640DC81E4800C0870404D" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Push to place the media shaft back on the winder. Make sure it clicks in place. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_E79D366579C7429B977E70F07D6F9EFE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EEC4E959-03B0-47B2-8D2C-6838527CD34F-low.png" id="IMAGE_AAD49296247240D1A08D630F57A7D1EE" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EEC4E959-03B0-47B2-8D2C-6838527CD34F-low.png"/></fig></info></step></steps><postreq id="GUID-DE2DC4AF-338B-4C14-BADB-98AFFB9DABC0" class="- topic/section task/postreq "><p class="- topic/p ">You can now wind media onto the core, for more information see 
<xref keyref="19FUNC030" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-185DF587-7FB8-49A8-8BF3-626091680E7F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 19 Print and wind without a tension bar?>19 Print and wind without a tension bar</xref>, 
<xref keyref="19FUNC040" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-BF953262-8898-4AFC-B545-338FAC9B091E.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 19 Print and wind with a tension bar?>19 Print and wind with a tension bar</xref>, 
<xref keyref="19FUNC050" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B5C11BED-C928-4685-96AE-0B0949CC35A9.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 19 Print and wind with a locked tension bar?>19 Print and wind with a locked tension bar</xref>. 
</p></postreq></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-77E3E148-DF16-4838-9432-CE905B393B0C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
